title: Bug 110566: Wrong data set result returned when an invalid filter expression 'row[0]' is set
description: When setting a filter expression like 'row[0] equals to 0' or simply returning a null result set, the incorrect data set result is returned.
OB: When setting an invalid filter expression 'row[0] equals to 0' or returning a null result set, the data set result is incorrect.
EB: The data set result should be correct when an invalid filter expression 'row[0] equals to 0' is set or a null result set is returned.
SR: To reproduce the issue: 1. Set an invalid filter expression 'row[0] equals to 0' 2. Retrieve the data set result. Ensure that it is incorrect.
